<br>
So how do we fix this predicament. Yeah sure, the enchanters have the mastery of making enchanted jewelry to increase the potential of the stats of the wearer.  And the magicians have the abilities to summon items of power that were only bound onto the world of Norrath until the player expired of fatigue and left the world. But what about research? out of the game concept, the masters of wizardry, who spent their times learning and research the knowledge of Magic itself, was able to channel their focused energies and abilities into items of power.<br>
<br>
Research can be used to implement this. Given a new spell, channel item (wiz, mag, enc, nec), this spell would be used to ready the item to be made magical. We can limit the type of item per class (Ex: Class specific items), or even expand the classes the other pure caster classes but to a lesser degree for them since their research skill will be hindered by the non-use of research spells.<br>
<br>
Ex: One of the wizzies research spells is Enstill. We take the Channel Item spell on a staff (using basic example) . The staff becomes &quot;Channeled Staff&quot;. Now take the Channeled Staff, and the 2 research runes (Neglect &amp; Oppression) &amp; combine all 3 items into the research book. If successful the item can be called Staff of Enstillment.<br>
<br>
Now how do we balance this skill out: The most common way is like all trade skills: trivial levels. Certain spells on certain items would have a trivial level. Where as the 16th level research spells would be fairly common to be trivial at in Channeling items, where as the 49th level spells will have a harder time on succeeding. Also with this new skill, we can add extra research items to incorporate more spells and higher up spells past the 49th mark. Also ways of balancing out is use of charges on the items. You may say CHARGES, HOW DARE YOU!!!, but alas lemme explain this.<br>
<br>
Let's go with the example we used. Staff of Enstillment. If we use the basic staff found in the newbie area, or maybe a special staff that dropped with similar commonality. The use of Research to make the item would be say 5 charges. Now we take the same spell but channel maybe the equivalent of a bronze staff, it may have 10 charges instead of 5, but it is on a higher scale of difficulty to make and maybe have a longer duration on the spell. No if we take this same idea with maybe a very higher staff (velium for example) the charges can be brought up to 20.<br>
But if we use the charges idea, why would people pay for these items. There has to be some leeway with this. Would the item be useless after the charges go away. Maybe or maybe not. People use 10 charge sow potions, and keep coming back for more. But why, because the usefulness of sow is always needed. People may not like the idea of charges with enstill or other type of spells, but give a warrior trying to solo. Enstill may be something good for the user, kind of something that can be used to get away with easy.<br>
<br>
Another way people can using this skill is combining sets of runes to make double effecting or triple effecting items. The research book may need to be expanded to maybe 6 or 8 slots for this, but may be well worth it. give the same example. use boots instead of a staff. Channel the boots and combine in the research book Attraction &amp; Expulsion (Levitate), Neglect &amp; Oppression (Enstill) and the Channeled Boots. The resulting item would be Boots of airy grasp. The research skill on this item would be harsh, but add a perma effect of lev with 10 charges of enstill.<br>
<br>
Lastly on this, items that can be used other than runes that can increase durations,distances and other manipulations. Why do this? because common sense. In old tales of myth, the practicioners of magic used items like pentagrams, hearts of fell beasts, and other items of the like to increase the powerfulness of the items in which they were creating. They were considered as &quot;focus items&quot;. Means of channeling items into a more devastating power source. Items like these in combination of runes and the channeled items, produce more powerful effects.<br>
<br>
Just promise to read this and take it into concept. Remember this is Just an idea<br>
