<br>
You could combine certain spells at certain levels, and get Held items that would add stats and whatnot.<br>
<br>
For instance:<br>
<br>
To make a basic Book, you'd combine your level 16 researched spells into a &quot;Apprentice Manual&quot;. Then combine your level 20 spells into a &quot;Advanced manual&quot;. Combine the two and you'd get a Book with stats that you could use/sell. The books you create would be used in the recipes of the more advanced books (like the Velious Quests), and should be class based (I.E. Wizards could only make Books for Wizzies, Necros would only make books for Necros).<br>
<br>
The idea behind making them class based is so you couldn't make too much of a profit on them. In fact, they could even be no-drop (yah yah, I know...).<br>
<br>
I agree research should be more of a class tradeskill like Alchemy. I just wish VI saw it that way. <p><center><br>Jarnin Fisheermann<Br><b>Disciple of Hate<Br><b>Rallos Zek</b><Br></b><Br>Grand Master Fisherman<Br>Master Brewer<Br>Master Chef<Br>Master of Begging</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umdarkelf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mdar kelf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/24/01 11:54:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=503.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestive ideas on research skill</span><hr size=1> this would be great to have!!<br>
